              ],
              "free_text": [
                " NaI(Tl) crystal."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Stacks of 4-mil polyethylene foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The experiment was performed by",
                "bombarding polyethylene foils with about 1/100",
                "microampere of 20-MeV deuterons for periods of the",
                "order of 30 minutes, during which time the beam",
                "current was held constant to better than 10%. After",
                "the bombardment the individual foils were trapped",
                "between aluminum sheets of thickness adequate to",
                "absorb the positrons of N13 and C11, and the decay",
                "was followed over many half-lives by counting the",
                "annihilation quanta with an NaI(Tl) crystal. (Neither",
                "body gives nuclear gamma rays.)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " All decay curves were analyzed to find the",
                "relative amounts of N13 and C11 present in each foil",
                "at the end of the irradiations. The surface densities",
                "of the polyethylene foils were determined by weighing",
                "small triangles cut from the bombarded region of each",
                "foil; they were constant to within 2 percent from",
                "foil to foil and no correction was necessary on",
                "account of variations in surface density. With these",
                "data, relative cross sections for the (d,n) and (d,t)",
                "reactions were computed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": 50.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The absolute cross section scale,",
                "however, was not set up with great care and may be in",
                "error by as much as 50 percent."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The relative amounts of N13 and C11 were corrected",
                "for the finite duration of the bombardments."
              ]
            }
          ],
